From: Robert Bruce Findler <robby@cs.uchicago.edu>
To: steck@ccs.neu.edu
Cc: bugs@plt-scheme.org
Subject: RE: all/5820: License link should point to servlet
Date: Fri, 13 Sep 2002 15:11:59 -0500 (CDT)

 A while back, I had asked you for a way to go to a page that would work
 better than what I'm forced to use. I wanted an interface that would
 tkae, for example, a manual name and and an index/keyword entry in the
 manual and go to that place. You did that part, I think. I also wanted
 something that would go to particular places, such as the release notes
 and the tour. That hasn't materialized yet, so I just had those stubs
 in there. I guess the communication got lost somehow.
 
 In any case, I would like to see that the help desk library exports
 procedures like goto-tour and goto-release-notes that do the right
 thing with frames, etc. also, that means that if the locations of these
 things change, Drscheme doesn't need to change, only the help desk
 needs to change.
 
 Does that sound okay?
 
 Robby
 
